    • Constructor Detail

      • JavaParameterSpec

        public JavaParameterSpec(java.lang.String packageName,
                         java.lang.String className,
                         java.lang.String halfSignature,
                         int paramIdx)
        Creates a new instance of the RIFLDocument.JavaParameterSpec class
        Parameters:
        packageName - The name of the Java package containing the class which contains the method whose parameter is being configured as a source or sink.
        className - The name of the class containing the parameter to be defined as a source or sink.
        halfSignature - The method name and the formal parameters with fully-qualified names in brackets. This is like a Soot subsignature, except for the return type which is omitted.
        paramIdx - The index of the parameter to be defined as a source or sink. 0 refers to the return value, so the list is 1-based.
